parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall while driving, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents. The vehicle may not restart until it has cooled down, which can take at least an hour.
symptoms: the engine does not start until it has cooled down
the fuel pump makes a noise for 20 minutes when the key is not in the ignition
the fuel pump fails to produce a whirring sound when trying to start the engine.
